President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Idaho and ordered Federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in response to the COVID-19 pandemic. This declaration provides Federal funding for emergency protective measures, including direct assistance, to all areas in Idaho impacted by the virus. Michael F. O'Hare has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas, and additional designations may be made in the future if requested by the State and deemed necessary. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.